post_text:
This is a quick update regarding the most recent COVID-19 information that is on the state website and is being discussed throughout our school community.

As of this morning we have a 21.9% positivity rate for Howard County which has caused some questions regarding why are students still in school. Over 50% of the latest positivity rate is based on a concentrated outbreak at one of our long term care facilities. There have been 115 cases reported for Howard County with 52 reported as recovered per the Iowa COVID-19 website. I have frequent contact with Audrey Nosbisch from the Howard County Dept of Health and any decision we would have to make in regards to school closure would be made in partnership with her recommendation. At this time there is not a concern for students attending school due to the fact that the concentration of positive cases is in one location.

Following Sunday’s recommendation by Gov. Reynold’s with the collaboration of the Iowa Department of Public Health to close all of Iowa’s schools for a period of 4 weeks, Howard-Winneshiek Community Schools will be closed for four weeks or until further notice starting Tuesday, March 17th. This includes all normal school day activities and all extra-curricular activities.

We will continue to provide updates to our families, staff and school community as more information becomes available. Thank you for your understanding during this time.

Buehler's Dynamite Doers
January 29 at 8:51 PM ·

Science Mystery 1: If you floated down a river, where would you end up? Using a paper model, the highest places were colored with thick marker lines. Then water was sprayed several times (rain) and observed to see where the water ended up. It was proven that water flows from high places to low places just as our real rivers start in high places and they flow downhill to the lowest places which are the oceans.

post_text:
Each year Crestwood Elementary has Lifetouch Photography come into the building and take our elementary student pictures. For the 2019-20 school year, we are changing our schedule. Instead of taking the pictures during the school year, we are having them taken during back to school conferences on Tuesday, August 20 from 10:00am-6:00pm. Please note that preschool pictures will still be taken during the school year as they are not in attendance at back to school conferences.

If you forget or are unable to have pictures taken during back to school conferences, students will be photographed during the retake date in September/October. It is our hope that by making this transition that there will be less lost instructional time due to picture taking and we will have a better quality photo for you. Please call the office if you have any questions 563-547-2340.

Mrs. Grimm, Crestwood Elementary Principal
